title: Dining with the Chef Mini
subTitle: The techniques, ingredients and harmony of Japanese food recipes in just five minutes. Chef Rika cooks alongside master chef Tatsuo Saito to show viewers how to prepare delicious Japanese dishes at home.

title: NHK Newsline
subTitle: Hourly news updates featuring current affairs, business news, financial updates and global weather forecasts.

title: Time and Tide
subTitle: Highlights a variety of historical events with a keen focus on the ties between Japan and other countries, and explores complex worldwide movements from the perspective of Japanese history.

title: The Seasons of Yamato
subTitle: The coldest period of the year is called `Kan', meaning midwinter. Another expression for this time of the year as `Kan no iri', meaning entering midwinter. `Shoukan' used for this term is 'Kan' which is 'shou', 'shou' meaning small or less.

title: NHK World Japan
subTitle: Edo was a city of waterways. The Yoroi Ferry transported people across the Nihonbashi River, one of its main commercial arteries. For the captain, it was a high-pressure job requiring skill and guts.

title: Grand Sumo Highlights
subTitle: Sumo highlights from a range of tournaments that have taken place across the globe. Sumo is one of the most traditional Japanese sports and boasts a history going back more than 1500 years.

title: Sumopedia
subTitle: Explores the story behind how people strengthened the sumo ring in ancient time by using special parts filled with sand called tokudawara.

title: NHK Newsline
subTitle: Hourly news updates featuring current affairs, business news, financial updates and global weather forecasts.

title: Spiritual Explorers
subTitle: Koyasan is a revered Buddhist temple complex built on a towering mountain. Through rituals and meditation, our explorer seeks to discover the Buddha within us all.

title: Japan Delish
subTitle: Curry rice, one of Japan's most iconic national dishes. Why is this dish, born in India, so beloved by the Japanese?

title: BOSAI: Science That Can Save Your Life
subTitle: A look at some of Japan's emergency food options which are intended to meet the needs of various people. Also, a look at the rolling stock method, a smart way to stockpile emergency food.

title: Design Museum Japan
subTitle: The team meet Hishikawa Seiichi, a Japanese video and craft artist, in Tottori Prefecture to explore fishing flags with colourful, hand-drawn designs.

title: NHK Newsline
subTitle: Hourly news updates featuring current affairs, business news, financial updates and global weather forecasts.

title: Hikikomori Pilgrimage
subTitle: Five young men from around Japan, once withdrawn from society, a phenomenon known as hikikomori, embark on a 1,200-kilometer pilgrimage around the island of Shikoku, on a journey of self-discovery.
